here's what you can safely edit vs. what you should avoid:

## **SAFE TO EDIT** (Content & UI Files):

**Page Content:**

- `app/page.tsx` - Main homepage content and layout
- `app/trade/page.tsx` - Trading page content
- `app/lend/page.tsx` - Lending page content
- `app/profile/page.tsx` - Profile page content


**Components (Your Custom Content):**

- `components/dashboard/opensea-dashboard.tsx` - Main dashboard layout
- `components/opensea/opensea-header.tsx` - Header navigation
- `components/trading/swap-interface.tsx` - Trading interface
- `components/lending/lending-markets.tsx` - Lending platform
- `components/profile/wallet-info.tsx` - Profile sections
- Any other components in `/components/dashboard/`, `/components/opensea/`, `/components/trading/`, etc.


**Styling:**

- `app/globals.css` - Colors, themes, and custom styles (be careful with the base theme variables)


## Ô∏è **BE CAREFUL** (System Files):

- `app/layout.tsx` - Only edit metadata/title, avoid changing the structure
- `package.json` - Only add dependencies if needed, don't remove existing ones


## **DO NOT EDIT** (Core System Files):

- `components/ui/*` - Pre-built UI components (button, card, etc.)
- `hooks/use-mobile.tsx` - System hooks
- `hooks/use-toast.ts` - Toast functionality
- `lib/utils.ts` - Utility functions
- `next.config.mjs` - Next.js configuration
- `tsconfig.json` - TypeScript configuration


**Rule of thumb:** Edit files in your custom folders (`/dashboard/`, `/opensea/`, `/trading/`, `/lending/`, `/profile/`) and page files, but avoid touching the `/ui/`, `/hooks/`, and `/lib/` system folders.